  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: A_poison_blooms_in_grove_alush
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 135
  mythName: A poison blooms in grove alush
  omens:
  - '1. A calm glade amid dense trees. Complete

    silence. Three empty plinths,
    one each in

    black, grey, and white stone. Anyone

    attempting to leave
    the clearing finds

    themselves back within it until an

    offering is left
    on each plinth, regardless

    of its value.'
  - '2. In the Glade, the White Stone Hunter

    asks "whom shall I aid?" to whoever
    left

    their offering. They vanish and perform a

    kind act to that person.'
  - '3. In the Glade, the white offering

    is returned.'
  - '4. In the Glade, the Grey Stone Hunter asks

    "whom shall I punish?" to whoever
    left

    their offering. They vanish and perform a

    punishment, the effects
    lasting until the

    next Spring (see opposite).'
  - 5. In the Glade, the grey offering is returned.
  - '6. In the Glade, the Black Stone Hunter asks

    "whom shall I kill?" to whoever
    left their

    offering. They vanish and attempt to kill

    that person. The
    offering is left on the

    body of the target if killed.'
  verse: 'Omens

    1. A calm glade amid dense trees. Complete

    silence. Three
    empty plinths, one each in

    black, grey, and white stone. Anyone

    attempting
    to leave the clearing finds

    themselves back within it until an

    offering
    is left on each plinth, regardless

    of its value.

    2. In the Glade, the
    White Stone Hunter

    asks "whom shall I aid?" to whoever left

    their offering.
    They vanish and perform a

    kind act to that person.

    3. In the Glade,
    the white offering

    is returned.

    4. In the Glade, the Grey Stone Hunter
    asks

    "whom shall I punish?" to whoever left

    their offering. They vanish
    and perform a

    punishment, the effects lasting until the

    next Spring
    (see opposite).

    5. In the Glade, the grey offering is returned.

    6.
    In the Glade, the Black Stone Hunter asks

    "whom shall I kill?" to whoever
    left their

    offering. They vanish and attempt to kill

    that person. The
    offering is left on the

    body of the target if killed.

    Cast

    Based
    on the offering left at their plinth.

    White Stone Hunter, Serephyllea

    VIG
    12, CLA 12, SPI 16, 8 GD

    A2 (silent mail, silver plate)

    Hunting spear
    (1d10 to 3d10, made from the

    material of their offering)

    Grey Stone
    Hunter, Gravok

    VIG 13, CLA 15, SPI 12, 8 GD

    A2 (heavy cloak, round
    helm)

    Hunting bow (1d8 to 3d8, arrows made from

    the material of their
    offering)

    Black Stone Hunter, Therenas

    VIG 13, CLA 16, SPI 17, 8 GD

    Armour
    2-4 (armour made from the material

    of their offering)

    Scythe blade
    (2d10 or 2d8 blast, long)

    Amid the stillen halt and hush'
  castEntries:
  - name: White Stone Hunter, Serephyllea
    statBlock: 'VIG 12, CLA 12, SPI 16, 8 GD

      A2 (silent mail, silver plate)'
    notes: 'Hunting spear (1d10 to 3d10, made from the

      material of their offering)'
  - name: Grey Stone Hunter, Gravok
    statBlock: 'VIG 13, CLA 15, SPI 12, 8 GD

      A2 (heavy cloak, round helm)'
    notes: 'Hunting bow (1d8 to 3d8, arrows made from

      the material of their
      offering)'
  - name: Black Stone Hunter, Therenas
    statBlock: 'VIG 13, CLA 16, SPI 17, 8 GD

      Armour 2-4 (armour made from
      the material'
    notes: 'of their offering)

      Scythe blade (2d10 or 2d8 blast, long)

      Amid
      the stillen halt and hush

      A poison blooms in grove alush

      ARBITRARY
      PUNISHMENT

      Immediate Effect Later Effect

      1 Best clothes stolen
      Eyes fall out

      2 Hiccups Constant coldness

      3 Spoiled food Loss
      of taste

      4 Slippery hands Broken limb

      5 Hair falls out Severed
      hand

      6 Annoying insects Teeth fall out

      Glade

      Dwelling:
      Silk farm ~ Sanctum: Salt grotto ~ Monument: Seer bone reliquary

      Hazard:
      Pouncing spiders ~ Curse: Tangling shadows ~ Ruin: Torn tapestry

      Th'
  flavorTable:
    title: ARBITRARY PUNISHMENT
    rows:
    - 1 Best clothes stolen Eyes fall out
    - 2 Hiccups Constant coldness
    - 3 Spoiled food Loss of taste
    - 4 Slippery hands Broken limb
    - 5 Hair falls out Severed hand
    - '6 Annoying insects Teeth fall out

      Glade'
  dwelling: Silk farm
  sanctum: Salt grotto
  monument: Seer bone reliquary
  hazard: Pouncing spiders
  curse: Tangling shadows
  ruin: Torn tapestry
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
